<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="jn0056a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn0" href="#jn0056">JN0: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/jn0all.htm#jn0056a"> (I.A) 56(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> She comes at night when the city is still; <br>invisible, inaudible, all unsummoned. She <br>comes from her ancient seat to visit the <br>least of her children, mother most venerable, <br>as though he had never been alien to her. <br>She knows the inmost heart; therefore <br>she is gentle, nothing exacting; saying, <br>I am susceptible of change, an imaginative <br>influence in the hearts of my children. <br>Who has pity for you when you are sad <br>among the strangers? Years and years I <br>loved you when you lay in my womb.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="jn0056a"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/lexq.htm#j0056a">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/q86.htm#jn0056a">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/q86.htm#jn0056a">1986 (15.4196)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/l22q.htm#jn0056a">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#jn0056a">MS V.A.19-31v</ms> </li><li>JJA 14:256 </li><li><a name="q2G1d" href="../udra/u15da.htm#q2g1d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/q2g1d.htm#jn0056a">Draft: 15&sect;2G.1</a></li> </ul> <ul class="list-inline" id="jn0056a"></li><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/lexq.htm#j0056a">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/q86.htm#jn0056a">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/q86.htm#jn0056a">1986 (15.4203f)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/l22q.htm#jn0056a">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#jn0056a">MS V.A.19-31v</ms> </li><li>JJA 14:256 </li><li><a name="q2G1d" href="../udra/u15da.htm#q2g1d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/q/q2g1d.htm#jn0056a">Draft: 15&sect;2G.1</a></li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Silverman/La Hune no. XV. A copy of this epiphany made by Stanislaus Joyce can be found at Cornell 17 p.43. Stanislaus Joyce writes that this &ldquo;dream-epiphany&rdquo; was recorded by Joyce on his Paris sojourn in 1902-3 (see <cite>My Brother&apos;s Keeper</cite>, pp. 229-30).</mm> </dd></dl>
